President Barack Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. These appointments include Jay C. Shambaugh as a member of the Council of Economic Advisers, M. Tia Johnson as Assistant Secretary for Legislative Affairs at the Department of Homeland Security, Doreen E. Brown and Aaron Payment as members of the National Advisory Council on Indian Education, Joan McDonald as a member of the National Infrastructure Advisory Council, Lisa Funderburke Hoffman as a member of the National Museum and Library Services Board, and Carmen Amalia Corrales as a member of the President's Commission on White House Fellowships. President Obama expressed confidence in these individuals and their ability to tackle the challenges facing America.